  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Matthew Henry's Concise Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "26:1-12 How soon do unholy hearts lose the good impressions convictions have made upon them! How helpless were Saul and all his men! All as though disarmed and chained, yet nothing is done to them; they are only asleep. How easily can God weaken the strongest, befool the wisest, and baffle the most watchful! David still resolved to wait till God thought fit to avenge him on Saul. He will by no means force his way to the promised crown by any wrong methods. The temptation was very strong; but if he yielded, he would sin against God, therefore he resisted the temptation, and trusted God with the event.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Barnes' Notes on the Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Ahimelech the Hittite - Only mentioned here. Uriah was also a Hittite.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Abishai - He was son of Zeruiah, David's sister, but probably about the same age as David. He because very famous as a warrior 2 Samuel 23:18, but was implicated with his brother Joab in the murder of Abner in retaliation for the death of their brother Asahel 2 Samuel 3:30. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "Abishai - He was son of Zeruiah, David's sister, but probably about the same age as David. He because very famous as a warrior ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 23:18",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", but was implicated with his brother Joab in the murder of Abner in retaliation for the death of their brother Asahel ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Samuel 3:30",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ". ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "",
            "children": []
          }
        ]
